The paper discusses the use of Interactive Artificial Intelligence in the domain of interactive software design, which involves human subjective judgment. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of different meta-heuristic search algorithms for this problem, indicating that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the representation of candidate solutions, which suggests that it may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
